derived_ev: "Denali" originates from the Koyukon Athabaskan language (Dina'li in Koyukon), meaning "the high one" or "the great one"
The Koyukon people, specifically the Lower Koyukuk River band of Athabaskan-speaking Indigenous Alaskans, have used the name "Denali" for centuries to refer to the mountain
The U.S. Board on Geographic Names formally adopted the name "Denali" in 2015 to honor Koyukon Athabaskan heritage
The indigenous group historically associated with the name "Denali" is the Koyukon Athabaskan people
